# Styling Rules

## Token Usage
Always import tokens via `@use` — never hardcode raw values.

| Token file | Import alias |
|---|---|
| `@/styles/tokens/colors` | colors |
| `@/styles/tokens/spacing` | spacing |
| `@/styles/tokens/typography` | typography |
| `@/styles/tokens/radius` | radius |
| `@/styles/tokens/shadows` | shadows |

```scss
// ✅
@use '@/styles/tokens/spacing' as *;
@use '@/styles/tokens/typography' as *;
padding: $spacing-4;
font-size: $font-size-sm;

// ❌
padding: 16px;
font-size: 14px;
```

## Theme-Aware Values
Use CSS custom properties for anything that should change between light and dark themes.

```scss
// ✅ — adapts to theme automatically
color: var(--color-text);
background: var(--color-surface);
border-color: var(--color-border);

// ❌ — hardcoded, breaks dark mode
color: #111827;
```

Available custom properties are defined in `src/styles/theme/light.scss` and `dark.scss`.

## Selectors
- Use BEM-style modifiers: `.block--modifier`
- Keep nesting shallow (max 3 levels)
- Scope interactive states (`:hover`, `:focus`) inside the base class block
- Gate hover/active states with `:not(:disabled)` for accessible components
